data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In EF Core 11, the **sync-over-async opt-in for the Cosmos DB provider is removed entirely**. The Cosmos SDK is inherently async-only, so EF Core no longer wraps async calls in synchronous wrappers.

All four of your methods will throw `InvalidOperationException` at runtime:

| Sync (breaks) | Async (replacement) |
|---|---|
| `ToList()` | `ToListAsync()` |
| `First(...)` | `FirstAsync(...)` |
| `Count()` | `CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `SaveChangesAsync()` |

## Fix

Convert to async throughout:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

Callers must also be updated to `await` these methods — async propagates up the call chain. There is no configuration flag to restore the old behavior in EF Core 11.
